# Tasks - 10th day
## Task 1. Fix the bash program

Fix the bash program so that it will

- at startup, display the welcome text "Welcome to SuperBash" and just before leaving the program "Goodbye".
- instead of the message "command not found" with the wrong command printed "command does not exist"
- in addition to the "exit" command to exit the shell, the "end" command should also work
- that the "cd" command will only work if the target folder does not contain the letter a; when calling, for example, "cd programs" (the name "programs" contains the letter a), the shell should display "Can't change to target folder. I am allergic to 'a'"
Example of how a "fixed" bash program works:  

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)


Technical instructions for obtaining the source code and translating the bash project:

- download the source code of the [bash-5.0.tar.gz](http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/bash/bash-5.0.tar.gz) program from the [website](http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/bash/) and unpack it with the tar xvzf bash-5.0.tar.gz command
- fix the appropriate files in the bash-5.0 folder
- compile the program with ./configure and make
- compiled program run with ./bash
